=========================================================
5-DAY DSA ROADMAP + PATTERN RECOGNITION QUESTIONS
TARGET: 10+ YEARS C++ INTERVIEWS
=========================================================

RULE:
Solve all PRIMARY questions first.

Then solve PATTERN RECOGNITION questions WITHOUT
looking at topic names.

If you can identify the pattern yourself,
you are interview-ready for that topic.

=========================================================
DAY 1 : ARRAYS + HASHING + TWO POINTERS
=========================================================

PRIMARY QUESTIONS
-----------------

1. Two Sum
2. Contains Duplicate
3. Valid Anagram
4. Group Anagrams
5. Top K Frequent Elements

6. Valid Palindrome
7. Two Sum II
8. Container With Most Water
9. 3Sum

PATTERNS
--------
✓ HashMap
✓ HashSet
✓ Frequency Counting
✓ Sorting
✓ Two Pointers

PATTERN RECOGNITION QUESTIONS
-----------------------------

1. Product Of Array Except Self
2. Longest Consecutive Sequence
3. 4Sum
4. Trapping Rain Water

Expected Recognition:
---------------------
Product Of Array Except Self  -> Prefix/Suffix
Longest Consecutive Sequence  -> HashSet
4Sum                          -> Sorting + Two Pointers
Trapping Rain Water           -> Two Pointers

=========================================================
DAY 2 : SLIDING WINDOW
=========================================================

PRIMARY QUESTIONS
-----------------

1. Best Time To Buy And Sell Stock
2. Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters
3. Longest Repeating Character Replacement
4. Permutation In String
5. Minimum Window Substring
6. Sliding Window Maximum

PATTERNS
--------
✓ Fixed Window
✓ Variable Window
✓ Frequency Map
✓ Monotonic Queue

PATTERN RECOGNITION QUESTIONS
-----------------------------

1. Maximum Sum Subarray Of Size K
2. Fruit Into Baskets
3. Subarrays With K Distinct Integers
4. Longest Ones After Replacement

Expected Recognition:
---------------------
Maximum Sum Subarray      -> Fixed Window
Fruit Into Baskets        -> Variable Window
K Distinct Integers       -> Variable Window
Longest Ones Replacement  -> Variable Window

